1 (2) For the purposes of this section, the department of
2 technology, management, and budget shall contract with 1 or more
3 providers to develop, supply, and score the Michigan merit
4 examination. The Michigan merit examination shall must consist of
5 all of the following:
6 (a) Assessment instruments that measure English language arts,
7 mathematics, reading, and science and are used by colleges and
8 universities in this state for entrance or placement purposes. This
9 shall include a writing component in which the pupil produces an
10 extended writing sample. The Michigan merit examination shall not
11 require any other extended writing sample.In selecting assessment
12 instruments to fulfill the requirements of this subdivision, the
13 department may consider the degree to which those assessment
14 instruments are aligned with this state's content standards.
15 (b) One or more tests from 1 or more test developers that
16 assess a pupil's ability to apply at least reading and mathematics
17 skills in a manner that is intended to allow employers to use the
18 results in making employment decisions. The department of
19 technology, management, and budget and the superintendent of public
20 instruction shall ensure that any test or tests selected under this
21 subdivision have all the components necessary to allow a pupil to
22 be eligible to receive the results of a nationally recognized
23 evaluation of workforce readiness if the pupil's test performance
24 is adequate.
25 (c) A social studies component.
26 (d) Any other component that is necessary to obtain the
27 approval of the United States Department of Education to use the
28 Michigan merit examination for the purposes of the no child left
29 behind act of 2001, Public Law 107-110, or the every student
