3
1 succeeds act, Public Law 114-95.
2 (3) In addition to all other requirements of this section, all
3 of the following apply to the Michigan merit examination:
4 (a) The department of technology, management, and budget and
5 the superintendent of public instruction shall ensure that any
6 contractor used for scoring the Michigan merit examination supplies
7 an individual report for each pupil that will identify for the
8 pupil's parents or legal guardians and teachers whether the pupil
9 met expectations or failed to meet expectations for each standard,
10 to allow the pupil's parents and teachers to assess and remedy
11 problems before the pupil moves to the next grade.
12 (b) The department of technology, management, and budget and
13 the superintendent of public instruction shall ensure that any
14 contractor used for scoring, developing, or processing the Michigan
15 merit examination meets quality management standards commonly used
16 in the assessment industry, including at least meeting level 2 of
17 the capability maturity model developed by the Software Engineering
18 Institute of Carnegie Mellon University for the first year the
19 Michigan merit examination is offered to all grade 11 pupils and at
20 least meeting level 3 of the capability maturity model for
21 subsequent years.
22 (c) The department of technology, management, and budget and
23 the superintendent of public instruction shall ensure that any
24 contract for scoring, administering, or developing the Michigan
25 merit examination includes specific deadlines for all steps of the
26 assessment process, including, but not limited to, deadlines for
27 the correct testing materials to be supplied to schools and for the
28 correct results to be returned to schools, and includes penalties
29 for noncompliance with these deadlines.
