1 the pupil at the high school at which the pupil receives high
2 school instruction, and the department shall include the pupil's
3 scores on the Michigan merit examination in the scores for that
4 high school for all purposes for which a school's or district's
5 results are reported. The department shall allow the middle college
6 program to use a 5-year graduation rate for determining adequate
7 yearly progress. As used in this subsection, "middle college" means
8 a program consisting of a series of courses and other requirements
9 and conditions, including an early college or other program created
10 under a memorandum of understanding, that allows a pupil to
11 graduate from high school with both a high school diploma and a
12 certificate or degree from a community college or state public
13 university.
14 (15) For each report that the department issues that includes
15 the statewide assessment results for a school building, the
16 department shall include the scores for the statewide assessment
17 and the graduation rate for consortium pupils with the scores for
18 the school building in the participating district in which the
19 consortium pupil is enrolled or would otherwise attend. The
20 statewide assessment for a consortium pupil may be administered
21 either at the consortium location or at the school building in the
22 participating district in which the consortium pupil is enrolled or
23 would otherwise attend. As used in this subsection, "consortium
24 pupil" means a pupil who is enrolled or participating in a
